<main class="container">
  <div class="page-header">
    <h1>{{subTitle}}</h1>
  </div>
  <section>
    <div id="userView">
      <p id="welcome">
        Welcome
        <span class="greeting">
          {{#if user}}
            {{user.firstName}}
            {{user.lastName}}
          {{else}}
            Guest
          {{/if}}
        </span>
      </p>
      <p>The NYC Motor Vehicle Good Samaritan Website is designed to provide an
        accessible plat-form for members of the public to share information
        about motor vehicle crashes with the NYPD, involved parties, and
        insurance companies.
      </p>
      <p>The goal of this website is to empower New York City residents and
        visitors to act as “Good Samaritans” by contributing eyewitness
        information that could assist in crash investigations, insurance claims,
        or legal proceedings.
      </p>
      <p>New York City’s dense population and constant flow of pedestrians,
        cyclists, and drivers make it a unique environment where many accidents
        are witnessed but not always reported. This platform bridges that
        gap—creating a centralized, transparent, and community-driven way for
        witnesses to share what they saw quickly and securely.
      </p>
      <p>Motor vehicle accidents remain one of the leading causes of premature
        death in the United States, with thousands of lives lost each year—many
        of them in urban areas like New York City. By encouraging timely and
        accurate witness reporting, this initiative aims not only to aid in
        post-crash accountability but also to promote safer driving behaviors
        and ultimately make our streets safer for everyone.
      </p>
      <p>Looking ahead, as autonomous vehicles and self-driving taxis become
        more common on city streets, the platform will also serve as a valuable
        public resource for monitoring, verifying,and improving the safety and
        accountability of these emerging transportation technologies.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</main>